Vice President Kamala Harris will attend the annual leaders' meeting of the Pacific Islands Forum virtually on July 12. She will emphasize the United States' dedication to the Pacific Islands region and explore ways to enhance U.S. involvement in the area. The Vice President will also discuss specific initiatives to benefit the people of the Pacific. Additionally, she will highlight the enduring relationship between the United States and the Pacific Islands and outline ongoing efforts to strengthen those ties. This engagement follows President Biden's address to the Pacific Islands Forum meeting in 2020 and Secretary Blinken's visit to Fiji earlier this year.